    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">倒塌</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>FALL so as to CEASE to STAND OR so as to be DESTROYED.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current words for the collapse of buildings is qǐng 傾 and huī 隳.</p>
<p>2. For the collapse of standing objects it is diān 顛.</p>
<p>3. For the collapse of mountains we have bēng 崩 and tuí 頹.</p>
<p>4. Dǎo 倒 is often used causatively to mean "make topple over".</p>
<p>5. Pū 仆 refers to things falling from a vertical position so as to take up a horisontal position.</p>
<p>6. Bì 斃 refers to some person or some animal collapsing suddenly, often to die.</p>
        </div>
